- Tailwind-first: use utility classes; prefer semantic tokens defined in `globals.css`.
- Variants: use CVA for complex components (see `button.tsx`).
- Theming: respect light/dark tokens; do not hardcode colors; use CSS variables when needed.
- Consistency: adhere to spacing/size scale; avoid ad-hoc arbitrary values if a token exists.
- Global styles: keep base minimal; no component-specific CSS in globals.

